### 4. **Confirmation Component** ⚠️
**Status**: ✅ Already installed, not used yet

**What it does**: Approval workflow for dangerous tool operations (delete, publish, spend credits).

**Why you need it**:
- Prevent accidental high-cost operations
- Add guardrails for expensive tools (e.g., 4K upscaling)
- Compliance for destructive actions
- User control over agent autonomy

**Implementation Example**:
```tsx
// In MessagePartRenderer.tsx
import {
  Confirmation,
  ConfirmationRequest,
  ConfirmationAccepted,
  ConfirmationRejected,
  ConfirmationActions,
  ConfirmationAction,
} from "@/components/ai-elements/confirmation";

// For expensive tools:
case "tool-upscaleImage": {
  if (part.approval) {
    return (
      <Confirmation approval={part.approval} state={part.state}>
        <ConfirmationRequest>
          This will use 50 credits to upscale to 4K. Continue?
        </ConfirmationRequest>
        <ConfirmationAccepted>✅ Approved upscaling</ConfirmationAccepted>
        <ConfirmationRejected>❌ Cancelled upscaling</ConfirmationRejected>
        <ConfirmationActions>
          <ConfirmationAction
            onClick={() => addToolApprovalResponse({ id: part.approval.id, approved: false })}
          >
            Cancel
          </ConfirmationAction>
          <ConfirmationAction
            onClick={() => addToolApprovalResponse({ id: part.approval.id, approved: true })}
          >
            Use 50 Credits
          </ConfirmationAction>
        </ConfirmationActions>
      </Confirmation>
    );
  }
}
```

**Backend changes needed**:
```typescript
// In upscaleImage tool definition
export const upscaleImage = tool({
  description: "Upscale image to 4K (50 credits)",
  inputSchema: z.object({ imageUrl: z.string() }),
  requireApproval: true, // ← Add this
  execute: async ({ imageUrl }) => {
    // ... upscaling logic
  },
});
```

**Files to modify**:
- `src/components/product/editor/agent/MessagePartRenderer.tsx`
- `src/lib/agents/tools/upscale-image.ts`
- `src/components/product/editor/agent/ChatClient.tsx` (import addToolApprovalResponse)

**Benefits**:
- ✅ Prevents accidental high-cost operations
- ✅ User control over spending
- ✅ Better trust and transparency

