## 📦 Medium Priority - Install When Needed

### 5. **Attachments Component**
**Status**: ❌ Not installed

**What it does**: Display file attachments in messages (images, PDFs, videos).

**Why you might need it**:
- If you add file upload to prompt input
- Show user-uploaded images before processing
- Display reference materials

**Install command**:
```bash
npx ai-elements@latest add attachments
```

**Use case**:
```tsx
// For user messages with attachments
import { Attachments, Attachment, AttachmentPreview } from "@/components/ai-elements/attachments";

{message.parts.map(part => {
  if (part.type === "file") {
    return (
      <Attachments variant="grid">
        <Attachment data={part}>
          <AttachmentPreview />
        </Attachment>
      </Attachments>
    );
  }
})}
```

**Benefits**:
- ✅ Professional file display
- ✅ Grid/inline/list variants
- ✅ Type-safe with AI SDK

